===pYtLoader.py===

The pYtLoader is a simple python script to download YouTube videos, and if needed save and tag the audio stream as mp3.

The pYtLoader uses software under the GPL (lame, faad2) so checkout:
http://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl.txt

This software is provided "AS IS", without any express or implied warranty in any kind.

The pYtLoader or any module...
...must NOT used for commercial products.
...must modified/adjusted/edited/copied/saved/deleted... etc. (do what you want to do)
...must be cleaned from spelling faults.

1) Requirements:
	python2
	wxpython (optimal for gui)
	lame
	faad2

2) How to use:
	2.1) GUI:
		Doubleclick on pYtLoader.py or execlude ./pYtLoader.py in a shell.
	2.3) Shell:
		Type in ./pYtLoader.py --help to see a complete list of arguments.
		i.e.:
			./pYtLoader -c --fullhd http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uxk4hIX3Kn4
			to download in fullHD and convert the audio stream to mp3.

3) Where are the files?!:
	~/YouTube/

